This paper is about knowledge graph reasoning, which involves machine learning, natural language processing, and databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new model that combines logic rules and neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, making cs.DB (Databases) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the inference of Markov Logic Networks, which is related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
